resources.description: Find accounts in the CRM system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all accounts whose name contains the word 'data', the search expression parameter will be where=name like '%data%'. If a search expression is not provided, then the first 100 records will be returned.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The only supported fields are 'lastModifiedDate', 'createdate' and 'domain'. The date fields need to be in ISO8601 format eg lastModifiedDate='2017-03-15T00:00:00.000Z' This api is restricted to the last 30 days by hubspot. The domain is a string such as 'cloud-elements.com'. Only one field can be used in the filter at a time

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of items returned in a query. Defaults to 100 if not supplied

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The token or link for getting the next page. This type of paging is a cursor based paging. Where you have to start at the beginning and traverse the result set.This value is supplied from the previous call in the Header 'Elements-Next-Page-Token

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Specify the fields (in csv) to return in the response payload. Defaults to all standard fields

parameters.description: Optional JSON Metadata that can contain useBatchUpload and maxNumberOfRecords. Passing {"useBatchUpload": "true"} will use the Hubspot batch API for the upload. resources.description: Find contacts in the CRM system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all contacts whose name contains the word 'data', the search expression parameter will be where=name like '%data%'. If a search expression is not provided, then the first 100 records will be returned.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. Valid filters are firstname, lastname and email. For example, email='coolrobot@hubspot.com'

parameters.description: Set this to true to use the fetch all endpoint at HubSpot to overcome a Hubspot issue that can return duplicate contacts between different pages. In order for this to be effective, the where clause above should be empty. If it is not, this parameter is ignored.
